                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee (Arms)/89:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-01T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 1, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 1—8:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>970. Your 468, January 31, noon. We are in accord with your understanding
                    expressed in the first sentence. The French, however, are not yet aware of the
                    details of the amendment of article 30 covered by your instruction of December
                    24.</p>
                <p>In the Paris meeting the civilian French officials appeared satisfied with our
                    suggestion to place civil aviation and all aeronautical engines in category V.
                    Since then we have learned that the French air officials desire inclusion of
                    aeronautical engines in category III a step which we cannot accept.</p>
                <pb facs="0112" n="10" xml:id="pg_10"/>
                <p>As soon as can learn the definite attitude of the French Government in the matter
                    we will inform you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
